sequenceDiagram
    title ZDAD-34: Overview Dashboard API

    participant User
    participant UI
    participant Backend as Backend<br/>(src/routes/overview_route.py)
    participant Database
    participant Jira

    %% Overview Endpoint
    User->>UI: Opens Dashboard landing page
    UI->>Backend: GET /api/v1/overview?period=last_month&specialization=devsecops
    Backend->>Backend: Decrypt token using private key
    Backend->>Jira: Validate Jira email from token
    Jira-->>Backend: User exists and is active
    Backend->>Backend: Validate query params (period, specialization)
    Backend->>Database: Fetch total projects count:<br/>COUNT(DISTINCT sn_project_id) WHERE not default<br/>+ COUNT(DISTINCT project_name) from tickets on default project
    Database-->>Backend: Return total projects count
    Backend->>Database: Fetch at_risk_threshold from settings<br/>WHERE specialization_id matches
    Database-->>Backend: threshold value
    Backend->>Database: Fetch projects WHERE<br/>current_date - onboarded_date > threshold<br/>AND not completed
    Database-->>Backend: Return at-risk projects + other KPI data
    Backend->>Database: Fetch status distribution from projects<br/>JOIN statuses WHERE is_active = 1
    Database-->>Backend: Return status counts per group
    Backend->>Database: Fetch top 5 overdue projects<br/>WHERE days since onboarding > threshold<br/>ORDER BY days overdue DESC
    Database-->>Backend: Return overdue projects list
    Backend->>Backend: Compute attention banner severity<br/>(critical > 5, warning 1-5, info 0)
    Backend->>Backend: Compute adoption rate percentage
    Backend-->>UI: 200 OK {metrics, statusDistribution,<br/>attentionBanner, mostOverdueProjects}
    UI-->>User: Display KPI tiles, charts,<br/>banner, and overdue list

    %% Specializations Endpoint
    User->>UI: Clicks specialization filter dropdown
    UI->>Backend: GET /api/v1/specializations
    Backend->>Backend: Decrypt token + validate Jira email
    Backend->>Database: SELECT specialization_id, specialization_name<br/>FROM specializations WHERE is_active = 1
    Database-->>Backend: Return specializations list
    Backend-->>UI: 200 OK {specializations: [{id, name}]}
    UI-->>User: Populate dropdown with specialization options

    %% Error Scenario
    Note over Backend,Database: On unhandled exception
    Backend->>Database: INSERT INTO error_log<br/>(error_message, error_function, stack_trace)
    Backend-->>UI: 500 - An unexpected error occurred
    UI-->>User: Display error message
